# Implementation checklist (125.md)

Use this checklist when implementing or reviewing the Sprint 2 chatbot. Tick items as done.

**Focus:** Domain-focused chatbot with advanced RAG + tool calling using Next.js and LangChain.

## Setup

- [x] Node on LTS (if needed)
- [x] pnpm installed; use it for this project
- [x] Next.js app created in current project folder
- [ ] Required dependencies installed (LangChain, OpenAI SDK, validation libs, vector DB libs)
- [ ] OpenAI API key obtained and stored securely (`.env.local`, never in code)

## Domain definition

- [ ] Domain/use case selected and documented (clear scope)
- [ ] Knowledge sources selected and added to `data/`
- [ ] Domain-specific system prompt and safety guardrails defined

## Core requirements (125.md)

### 1) RAG implementation

- [ ] Knowledge base ingestion pipeline implemented
- [ ] Chunking strategy configured and documented
- [ ] Embeddings-based retrieval implemented
- [ ] Similarity search working with relevant top-k retrieval
- [ ] Query translation/rewriting step implemented for better retrieval
- [ ] Response includes source context/citations where possible

### 2) Tool calling

- [ ] At least 3 domain-relevant tools implemented
- [ ] Tool input schemas validated (e.g. `zod`)
- [ ] Tool-call errors handled gracefully
- [ ] Tool results rendered clearly in the UI

### 3) Domain specialization

- [ ] Chatbot behavior is clearly specialized to chosen domain
- [ ] Domain-focused knowledge base integrated into responses
- [ ] Domain-specific safety/security considerations applied

### 4) Technical implementation

- [ ] LangChain integration implemented for model + retrieval workflow
- [ ] API route validation and sanitization implemented
- [ ] Proper error handling added (typed, safe responses)
- [ ] Logging/monitoring added (without leaking secrets)
- [ ] Rate limiting added for chat endpoint
- [ ] API key management follows secure env-var practices

### 5) User interface

- [ ] Intuitive chat interface implemented in Next.js
- [ ] Sources/citations displayed in responses
- [ ] Tool-call outputs displayed in dedicated UI area
- [ ] Progress/loading indicators shown for long operations

## Optional tasks (125.md)

### Easy

- [ ] Conversation history + export
- [ ] RAG process visualization
- [ ] Source citations in responses (if not already covered)
- [ ] Interactive help/chatbot guide

### Medium

- [ ] Multi-model support (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
- [ ] Real-time knowledge-base updates
- [ ] Advanced caching strategy
- [ ] Authentication + personalization
- [ ] Token usage and cost display
- [ ] Tool-call result visualization improvements
- [ ] Conversation export in PDF/CSV/JSON
- [ ] Connect to public remote MCP tools

### Hard

- [ ] Cloud deployment with scaling considerations
- [ ] Advanced indexing (e.g. RAPTOR, ColBERT)
- [ ] A/B testing for RAG strategies
- [ ] Automated knowledge-base updates
- [ ] Model fine-tuning for domain
- [ ] Multi-language support
- [ ] Advanced analytics dashboard
- [ ] Implement tools as MCP servers
- [ ] RAG evaluation (RAGAs or equivalent)

## Cross-project reviewer lessons (from Sprint 1)

- [ ] Prompt-injection defense added (treat user input as untrusted; delimit user text blocks; optionally use moderation)
- [ ] OpenAI/LangChain calls use timeout + retry settings; timeout returns user-friendly error
- [ ] Prompt-iteration evidence documented (comparison notes and rationale in docs)
- [ ] Unit tests added for validation and prompt/retrieval helpers
- [ ] At least one API integration test added with mocked model client
- [ ] Domain research documented in README or dedicated doc (niche choice, alternatives, target user need)
- [ ] Structured logging/observability added (latency, model/tool usage, token/cost metadata)
- [ ] Conversation context management added (sliding window and/or summarization to control token cost)

## Review readiness

- [ ] README updated with implemented `✅` items and evidence paths
- [ ] Lint passes
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] App runs locally and key flows are manually tested
